text: Tallahoma Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tallahoma is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "red rock". Variant names are "Tali Homma Creek", "Talla Homa Creek", and "Tallohoma Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jasper County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jones County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Newton County, Mississippi
title: Tallahoma Creek
